text.tspan: Share of dietary energy supply from fats vs. GDP per capita, 2022
The share of per capita dietary energy derived from fats, measured as the daily caloric supply from fat as a
percentage of total caloric supply, versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, adjusted for inflation and
differences in living costs between countries.
GDP per capita (international-$ in 2021 prices; plotted on a logarithmic axis)
Share of dietary energy from fats
Data source: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2024); Eurostat, OECD, IMF, and World Bank (2025)

Note: GDP per capita is expressed in
international-$
at 2021 prices.
